# Cursor Rules

## Overview
This repository contains an AI Playbook for developer tooling. Follow these rules when assisting with any task.

## Skill Routing
Before implementing any task, check the project type and load the relevant skill:

- React component work → read `ai-playbook/.github/skills/react-components/SKILL.md`
- Accessibility testing → read `ai-playbook/.github/skills/a11y-automation/SKILL.md`
- Node.js/TypeScript service → read `ai-playbook/.github/skills/node-typescript-service/SKILL.md`
- New skill creation → read `ai-playbook/.github/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md`
- AI tool setup → read `ai-playbook/.github/skills/ai-tool-setup/SKILL.md`

To detect the project type automatically, run:
```
node ai-playbook/tools/project-detect.mjs <targetFolder>
```

## Scope Enforcement
- Only modify files within the stated target project folder.
- Never traverse above the project root.
- Run `node ai-playbook/tools/scope-guard.mjs <targetFolder> <changedFiles...>` before finalizing changes.

## Code Style
- Use minimal diffs: change only the lines necessary.
- Do not reformat unrelated code or reorganize imports.
- Do not rename variables outside the task scope.
- Use forward slashes in all file paths.

## Frontend Standards (React + TypeScript)
- Functional components with explicit TypeScript interfaces for props.
- WCAG 2.2 Level AA accessibility required on all interactive elements.
- Semantic HTML preferred over ARIA overrides.
- Tailwind utility classes only — no inline styles or CSS modules.
- All new components require a corresponding test file using Vitest + React Testing Library.

## Backend Standards (Node.js/TypeScript)
- Async/await with typed request/response.
- Validate all inputs (Zod, Joi, or class-validator).
- Return structured error responses (success, error.code, error.message).
- Structured logging — no `console.log` in production code.

## Security
- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, or passwords.
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs.
- Use parameterized queries for database access.

## Testing
- Run `npm test` to execute the test suite.
- Run `npm run lint` for linting.
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` for type checking.

## Policy Files
For detailed rules, load:
- `ai-playbook/.github/copilot-instructions/workspace-policy.md`
- `ai-playbook/.github/copilot-instructions/frontend-policy.md`
- `ai-playbook/.github/copilot-instructions/backend-policy.md`
- `ai-playbook/.github/copilot-instructions/style-output.md`
